    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In Christi nomine. Anni ab incarnatione eiusdem MCLVI, tempore <persName
                            key="#Popes" ref="#people/4312">Adriani</persName> pape et <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/124">Frederici</persName> imperatoris,
                        secundo die exeuntis mensis iulii, indictione [...]. Donnus <persName
                            key="#Abbots" ref="#people/4310">Iohannes</persName> gracia Dei humilis
                            <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fundi #Mansi #Imperial/royal_diploma
                            #Assembly #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte <placeName ref="#places/4179"
                                >Pomposiane</placeName> ecclesie</orgName> ideo precepit mihi
                            <persName key="#Tabellio #Notary"><name ref="Petrusbonus">Petro
                                Bono</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellioni</rs> exemplare predictas cartas autenticas
                        quia, quando habebat placitum cum domino <persName key="#Bishops"
                            ref="#people/4313">Griffone</persName>
                        <placeName ref="#places/80"><orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1437"
                                >Ferrariensi</orgName></placeName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopo</rs> de <rs key="#Fundi">fundo</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Mansi #Imperial/royal_diploma
                            #Assembly"
                            ref="#estates/2411"><placeName
                                key="#Fundi #Mansi #Imperial/royal_diploma
                                #Assembly"
                                ref="#places/3594">Ruvine</placeName></geogName> et <geogName
                            key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/3975"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                >Rustizane</placeName></geogName>, in anno Domini millesimo CLVI,
                        venit quidam frater <persName><name ref="Andreas">Andreas</name></persName>
                        nomine de monasterio <orgName
                            key="#Fundi #Mansi #Imperial/royal_diploma
                            #Assembly #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3641">
                            <placeName ref="#places/4802">Sancti Adelberti</placeName></orgName>,
                        dedit pignus arbitris, videlicet dono <persName
                            key="#Potestas #Vir_clarissimus" ref="#people/4314">Salinguerra
                        </persName>, <rs key="#Vir_clarissimus">vir clarissimo</rs> de Ferraria,
                        electus <rs key="#Potestas">potestas</rs> a predicto episcopo et abbate et
                        ab omnibus emphyteoticariis de supradictis fundis, et a <persName
                            key="#Judge"><name ref="Rodulfus">Rodulfo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudice</rs>, filius <persName><name ref="Vicedominus"
                                >Vicedomini</name></persName>, qui erat electus arbiter a prefatis
                        dominis et ab enphyteoticariis, de omnibus peticionibus fundi Ruvine et
                        Rustizane unicuique petenti secundum racionem et bonum usum diffinire. Ipse
                        vero predictus frater Sancti Adelberti peciit a supradictis arbitris ut
                        darent ei, in vice sui monasterii, quasdam sortes et porciones de fundo
                        Ruvine, que releguntur in suo <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            >precepto</rs> facto a tercio <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma 
                            #Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/7">Ottone</persName> imperatore. Secundum racionem,
                        prefatus domnus abbas Pomposianus ita locutus est predictis arbitris, quod
                        monasterium Sancti Adelberti unquam in alico tempore in supradicto fundo
                        Ruvine debet habere, quia pomposiana ecclesia iam possederat totum fundum
                        Ruvine plusquam centum annorum a monasterio Sancti Adelberti; pro se et pro
                        suis successoribus fecit perpetualem cessionem et securitatem ac
                        transaccionem abbati <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1599"
                            >Geronimo</persName> et eius successoribus in perpetuum de omnibus rebus
                        in monasterium Pomposianum habebat et detinebat, vel alii per eum in aliis
                        quibuscumque locis detinebant, que releguntur in precepto monasterii Sancti
                        Adelberti. Post paucos autem die supradictus frater Andreas monasterii
                        Sancti Adelberti, audita sentencia diffinitiva a supradictis electis
                        arbitris esse prolata adversum donnum <persName><name ref="Albericus"
                                >Albericum</name></persName> … vel <placeName ref="#places/594"
                            >Ravenne</placeName> de causa que agebatur inter eum et abbatem
                        Pomposianum, videlicet quia petebat <rs key="#Mansi">viginti quinque
                            mansos</rs> terre in massa Ruvine … absolutum a peticione supradicti
                        abbatis <orgName>Sancti Vitalis</orgName>, recepto pignore, recensit. [+ Ego
                        Petrus Bonus De]i nutu tabellius [de <rs key="#Vici">vico</rs>] <placeName
                            key="#Vici" ref="#places/4696">Baurie</placeName> et <rs key="#Notary"
                            >notarius</rs> sancte Pomposiane ecclesie per iussionem domni Iohannis
                        venerabilis abbatis …a supradicta vidi et audivi in presencia multorum
                        bonorum hominum ita scripsi, complevi et absolvi.</ab>
                </div>
